{"id": "1523769577962606592", "channel_id": "1326453691527594035", "author_id": "332573289438380032", "author_name": "moyashi0672", "content": "- Helot + gmurphy + aurita + winkle doesn't need wheel to perform, just exalt being ready = you're dead, in case of barrier you just wait a bit for aurita's skill cards, even if the RNG doesn't hit barrier they will die due to sacrifice stacks\n\nThe problem mainly arise because Helot exalt damages kept being buffed without any nerfs and will persist, it doesn't matter if every supports around her gets nerfed, you just kill the units itself but not helot, so you make them unplayable in general just so helot change supports like it's no big deal", "timestamp": "2026-07-06T19:16:17.656000+00:00", "type": 19, "edited_timestamp": "2026-07-06T19:22:31.431000+00:00", "mentions": ["1437487264023318668"], "reply_to": "1523768304936816691"}
{"id": "1523771038687559810", "channel_id": "1326453691527594035", "author_id": "332573289438380032", "author_name": "moyashi0672", "content": "- Hameln gmurphy just spam exalt with magic hat on hameln so he can reshuffle his 0 cost to spam exalt again\n\nHe can spam like 4 exalt in 1 turn and with the sacrifice stacking it can go to something line around 48 dmg from hameln's exalt + 12 bleed stacks + 36 sacrifice stacks\n\nIt seems low but we haven't counted the possibility of gmurphy being able to exalt 2 times due to the amount of cards reshuffled making it 150% sacrifice stacking or vulnerable from winkle if they pick her, they can also just use corpo for enhance for more dmg", "timestamp": "2026-07-06T19:22:05.920000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2026-07-06T19:22:23.409000+00:00"}
